<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1773,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[151,427,1773,1799]" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref15182" refString="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2009) Three new genera of Oriental Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Zootaxa, 2204 (1), 19 - 36. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2204.1.2" type="journal article" year="2009">Hulcr &amp; Cognato (2009)</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hulcr &amp; Cognato" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[660,836,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ambrosiophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[660,836,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">Ambrosiophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hopkins" authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" box="[1000,1269,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ambrosiodmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1000,1167,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">Ambrosiodmus</emphasis>
Hopkins
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Eichhoff" authorityName="Eichhoff" authorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1323,1437,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">Xyleborus</emphasis>
Eichhoff
</taxonomicName>
that had a flat pronotal disc that lacked asperities, an antennal club 
<typeStatus box="[1042,1090,1809,1835]" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">type</typeStatus>
3 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Dole, S. A. &amp; Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[1167,1356,1809,1835]" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" pagination="568 - 584" refId="ref15113" refString="Hulcr, J., Dole, S. A., Beaver, R. A. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2007) Cladistic review of generic taxonomic characters in Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Systematic Entomology, 32, 568 - 584. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2007.00386. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
Hulcr 
<emphasis box="[1237,1285,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
) that is flattened and rounded, and a steep declivity. 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaver, R. A." box="[693,853,1845,1872]" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" pagination="531 - 548" refId="ref12370" refString="Beaver, R. A. (1976) The biology of Samoan bark and ambrosia beetles (Coleoptera, Scolytidae and Platypodidae). Bulletin of Entomological Research, 65, 531 - 548. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300006210" type="journal article" year="1976">Beaver (1976)</bibRefCitation>
reports that galleries of this species were closely associated with galleries of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Beeson)" authorityName="Rabaglia &amp; Beaver &amp; Johnson &amp; Schmaedick &amp; Smith" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Beeson" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[482,804,1881,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Beaverium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="swezeyi">
<emphasis box="[482,695,1882,1907]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">Beaverium swezeyi</emphasis>
(Beeson)
</taxonomicName>
, indicating possible mycocleptoparasitism, an ecological characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hulcr &amp; Cognato 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Hulcr &amp; Cognato" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[382,840,1917,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ambrosiophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,558,1917,1943]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">Ambrosiophilus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[571,832,1917,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref15233" refString="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2010) New genera of Palaeotropical Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae) based on congruence between morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 2717 (1), 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2717.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Hulcr &amp; Cognato 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, S. L. &amp; Bright, D. E." box="[848,1100,1917,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" pagination="1 - 1533" refId="ref18668" refString="Wood, S. L. &amp; Bright, D. E. (1992) A catalog of Scolytidae and Platypodidae (Coleoptera). Part 2. Taxonomic index. Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs, 13, 1 - 1533." type="journal article" year="1992">Wood &amp; Bright (1992)</bibRefCitation>
list this species in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ambrosiodmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ambrosiodmus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The species has the generic characters of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hulcr &amp; Cognato" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[721,897,1953,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ambrosiophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,897,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="179">Ambrosiophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is here transferred to that genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
